FuncDef: This command specifies the Ethertype expected when the port's encapsulation type is dot1q. Dot1q encapsulation is supported only on Ethernet interfaces.

ParaDef.Info:
Specifies the Ethertype to expect, in either decimal or hex. Values-1536 to 65535 (0x0600 to 0xffff). ParamDefault: Default- If the encap-type is dot1p, then the default is 0x8100.
If the encap-type is qinq, then the default is 0x8100.
